This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it deals with natural language processing and classification of text data. It also involves machine learning techniques such as under-sampling, feature selection, stacking, and ensembles of models, which are commonly used in the field of computational linguistics. 

The paper also involves techniques such as feature selection and ensembles of models, which are commonly used in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). 

Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with the classification of Wikidata revisions into vandalism and non-vandalism, which involves retrieving relevant information from the data. 

Cybersecurity (cs.CR) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with detecting vandalism, which is a form of cyber-attack. 

Finally, Database (cs.DB) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the classification of data into two categories, which involves storing and retrieving data from a database.
